📐 PROJECT RULES — FRAMEWORK7 + LARAVEL
1. GENERAL PRINCIPLES

Backend is the single source of truth

Frontend is a thin client

No business logic in UI

No trust in client input

2. FRONTEND RULES (Framework7)

Do NOT hardcode:

price

duration

expiration

All service config must come from API

Only handle:

UI

realtime display

user input

One entry point: /app

3. BACKEND RULES (Laravel)

API only

All monetary values calculated server-side

All expiration calculated server-side

Use DB transactions for:

payment confirmation

service activation

4. DATABASE RULES

No magic IDs

All relations explicit

Unique constraints for:

order_code

bank_txn_id

Soft delete only if necessary

5. REALTIME RULES

Private channels only

Auth before subscribe

Emit events server-side only

6. SEEDING RULES

Seeder must be:

idempotent

environment-safe

Default service must always exist

7. FUTURE EXTENSION RULE

When adding more plans:

Only add new rows in services

Frontend auto renders

No refactor of payment logic

8. FORBIDDEN ACTIONS

❌ Hardcode price in UI
❌ Hardcode plan id
❌ Confirm payment from client
❌ Skip DB transaction
❌ Public realtime channel

9. MAINTENANCE GOAL

A new developer must be able to:

Add a new plan

Without touching payment core

Without touching frontend logic

Without breaking existing orders